summary: In this context, ethylbenzene (EBZ) is identified as one of the most widely used volatile organic compounds (VOCs) in urban environments, alongside other chemicals like benzene and toluene. The discussion highlights the harmful effects of VOCs, including ethylbenzene, on health, particularly in relation to indoor exposure. However, the relationship is primarily categorical, as ethylbenzene is mentioned as part of a broader group of chemicals without specific interactions or detailed implications provided.
